# Backend API Configuration
# Point all services to your backend server
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3005
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3005
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=ws://localhost:3005
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3005

# Development Notes:
# - BACKEND_URL: Used for Next.js API routes (server-side)
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL: Used for client-side API calls (REST)
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL: Used for WebSocket connections
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_URL: Used for authentication endpoints
#
# All should point to the same backend server (typically port 3005 in dev)
# Frontend runs on port 3006 (configured in package.json)
